NAIROBI, Kenya, March 6, 2023/APO Group/ -- 
                                                        
                            On Friday, March 3, 2023, in response to an invitation from AU-IBAR, the Africa Network for Animal Welfare (ANAW) visited their premises. Prof. James Wabacha (representing AU-IBAR) awarded Josphat Ngonyo ANAW with an award of gratitude for the priceless relationship between ANAW and AU-IBAR that has lasted over a decade.
                                The AAWC is an annual conference co-hosted by experts and practitioners to discuss animal welfare, wildlife conservation, and environmental conservation concerns
                            



ANAW has cooperated with the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP), AU-IBAR, and the host country's government to organise the Africa Animal Welfare Conference (AAWC). The AAWC is an annual conference co-hosted by experts and practitioners to discuss animal welfare, wildlife conservation, and environmental conservation concerns.
Visit the conference website to find out more

The African Network for Animal Welfare has been crucial in working with communities, governments, partners, and other stakeholders across Africa to promote the humane treatment of all animals.